title: Inside Europe 23.06.2022
description: Election fallout in France, Dutch farmers protest livestock cuts to curb nitrogen, plus a report from the world’s longest running design Biennale in Ljubljana. Also: DW honors the last journalists in Mariupol, Spain plans legislation improving women’s access to abortion, Belgium reckons with its colonial past, plus a look at France’s trailblazing face-mask recycling project.
itunes:author: DW.COM | Deutsche Welle
itunes:keywords: Kate Laycock, French elections, Agriculture, Mariupol, photojournalism, Global Media Forum
